    <h2><u>Ratio Strength</u></h2>                    
                        
    <p><span><i>Ratio Strength </i></span>is another expression used for describing the concentration of a solution or a mixture. In expressing ratio strength it is customary to have the first figure as 1, followed by a colon and then another number, e.g, 1:100. The following definitions are helpful when working with a ratio strength preparations:</p>
    <p>Solids in liquids: 1 g of constituent in X ml of solution or liquid preparation. <br>
    Liquids in liquids: 1 ml of constituent in X ml of solution or liquid preparation.<br>
    Solids in solids: 1 gram of constituent in X g of mixture.</p>

     <br>
     
